{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01LeRJZ96TzxyTKeN3812ASi","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→{\n     2→  \"project\": \"Attention Span Test\",\n     3→  \"description\": \"A static web app that presents users with a battery of scientifically-grounded cognitive tests measuring attention, impulse control, and focus duration. Results are compared against pre-social-media-era baselines from published research, presented as a fun \\\"Brain Age\\\"-style score, and expandable into detailed scientific breakdowns. The app targets teenagers (13-20) and their parents, is mobile-first (iPhone/iPad), and generates shareable links by encoding results in the URL.\",\n     4→  \"userStories\": [\n     5→    {\n     6→      \"id\": \"US-001\",\n     7→      \"title\": \"App Shell and Navigation\",\n     8→      \"description\": \"As a user, I want a mobile-first app shell with smooth navigation between screens so that the experience feels native on my phone.\",\n     9→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n    10→        \"Landing page with app title, brief tagline, and \\\"Start Test\\\" CTA button\",\n    11→        \"Navigation flow: Landing -\\u003e Test sequence -\\u003e Results\",\n    12→        \"Mobile-first responsive layout that works on iPhone SE (375px) through iPad (1024px)\",\n    13→        \"Progress indicator showing which test you're on (e.g., \\\"Test 2 of 6\\\")\",\n    14→        \"Uses shadcn components for UI elements\",\n    15→        \"Built with Bun.serve() and HTML imports, React frontend\",\n    16→        \"Deploys to Vercel as a static site\"\n    17→      ],\n    18→      \"priority\": 1,\n    19→      \"passes\": false\n    20→    },\n    21→    {\n    22→      \"id\": \"US-002\",\n    23→      \"title\": \"Sustained Attention to Response Task (SART)\",\n    24→      \"description\": \"As a user, I want to take a sustained attention test where I tap for every digit except one, so that my ability to maintain focus and inhibit impulses is measured.\",\n    25→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n    26→        \"Digits 1-9 appear one at a time in the center of the screen at a fixed interval (~1150ms per stimulus, matching the original Robertson et al. 1997 protocol)\",\n    27→        \"User must tap/click for every digit EXCEPT the target digit (3)\",\n    28→        \"225 trials total (25 cycles of digits 1-9 in random order), taking ~4-5 minutes\",\n    29→        \"Records: commission errors (tapping on 3), omission errors (missing a non-3 digit), mean reaction time (ms), reaction time variability (coefficient of variation = SD/mean)\",\n    30→        \"Brief instruction screen before the test explaining what to do, with a practice round of 9 trials\",\n    31→        \"Baseline comparison: healthy adult commission error rate of 8-11%, mean RT of 332-375ms\",\n    32→        \"Results stored in sessionStorage upon completion\"\n    33→      ],\n    34→      \"priority\": 2,\n    35→      \"passes\": false\n    36→    },\n    37→    {\n    38→      \"id\": \"US-003\",\n    39→      \"title\": \"Focus Duration Test\",\n    40→      \"description\": \"As a user, I want to test how long I can sustain focus on a single piece of content before feeling the urge to skip, so I can see how my focus compares to pre-digital norms.\",\n    41→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n    42→        \"Presents a mildly engaging but not thrilling stimulus (e.g., a passage of text that slowly reveals, a slowly changing visual pattern, or a calm narrated story)\",\n    43→        \"User presses a \\\"I want to skip\\\" button whenever they feel the urge to move on\",\n    44→        \"Timer runs visibly only after test completes (not during, to avoid anchoring)\",\n    45→        \"Records: time until first skip urge, and whether they chose to continue or stop\",\n    46→        \"Baseline comparison: Gloria Mark's research - 2.5 minutes (2004) vs. 40 seconds (2020s median)\",\n    47→        \"Results stored in sessionStorage upon completion\"\n    48→      ],\n    49→      \"priority\": 2,\n    50→      \"passes\": false\n    51→    },\n    52→    {\n    53→      \"id\": \"US-004\",\n    54→      \"title\": \"Stroop Color-Word Test\",\n    55→      \"description\": \"As a user, I want to take a Stroop test that measures my ability to suppress automatic responses, so that my executive control is assessed.\",\n    56→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n    57→        \"Three conditions presented in sequence: (1) read color words in black ink, (2) name ink colors of colored rectangles, (3) name the ink color of incongruent color words (e.g., \\\"RED\\\" displayed in blue)\",\n    58→        \"Each condition: 20 stimuli, user selects from 4 color buttons (Red, Blue, Green, Yellow)\",\n    59→        \"Records: accuracy and mean RT per condition, interference score (condition 3 RT minus condition 2 RT)\",\n    60→        \"Brief instructions with 3 practice trials before the incongruent condition\",\n    61→        \"Baseline comparison: interference effect norms stratified by age group\",\n    62→        \"Results stored in sessionStorage upon completion\"\n    63→      ],\n    64→      \"priority\": 2,\n    65→      \"passes\": false\n    66→    },\n    67→    {\n    68→      \"id\": \"US-005\",\n    69→      \"title\": \"Psychomotor Vigilance Task (PVT)\",\n    70→      \"description\": \"As a user, I want to test my reaction time vigilance by responding to stimuli appearing at unpredictable intervals, measuring lapses in my attention.\",\n    71→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n    72→        \"A stimulus (e.g., a red circle or counter) appears at random intervals between 2-10 seconds\",\n    73→        \"User taps as fast as possible when the stimulus appears\",\n    74→        \"30 trials, taking approximately 2-3 minutes\",\n    75→        \"Records: median RT, number of lapses (RT \\u003e 500ms), number of false starts (tapping before stimulus)\",\n    76→        \"Baseline comparison: healthy adult median RT of ~250ms, lapse rate \\u003c 5%\",\n    77→        \"Results stored in sessionStorage upon completion\"\n    78→      ],\n    79→      \"priority\": 2,\n    80→      \"passes\": false\n    81→    },\n    82→    {\n    83→      \"id\": \"US-006\",\n    84→      \"title\": \"Delay Discounting Task\",\n    85→      \"description\": \"As a user, I want to make choices between smaller immediate rewards and larger delayed rewards, so that my impulse control and preference for instant gratification is measured.\",\n    86→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n    87→        \"Series of 20-27 binary choices: e.g., \\\"$50 now\\\" vs \\\"$100 in 30 days\\\"\",\n    88→        \"Amounts and delays adjust based on previous choices (staircase procedure) to find the indifference point\",\n    89→        \"Choices presented as large tappable cards, mobile-friendly\",\n    90→        \"Records: discount rate (k parameter from hyperbolic model), indifference points at multiple delays\",\n    91→        \"Baseline comparison: normative k values for adolescents from published literature\",\n    92→        \"Results stored in sessionStorage upon completion\"\n    93→      ],\n    94→      \"priority\": 3,\n    95→      \"passes\": false\n    96→    },\n    97→    {\n    98→      \"id\": \"US-007\",\n    99→      \"title\": \"Go/No-Go Task\",\n   100→      \"description\": \"As a user, I want to take a simple Go/No-Go test measuring my ability to withhold automatic responses, providing a quick measure of impulsivity.\",\n   101→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   102→        \"\\\"Go\\\" stimuli (e.g., green circles) appear frequently (80% of trials); \\\"No-Go\\\" stimuli (e.g., red circles) appear infrequently (20%)\",\n   103→        \"100 trials total, stimulus duration ~500ms, ISI ~1000ms, taking ~2.5 minutes\",\n   104→        \"User taps for Go stimuli, withholds for No-Go stimuli\",\n   105→        \"Records: commission error rate (tapping on No-Go), omission error rate, mean RT, RT coefficient of variation\",\n   106→        \"Baseline comparison: healthy adolescent commission error rate norms (decreases with age through ~16)\",\n   107→        \"Results stored in sessionStorage upon completion\"\n   108→      ],\n   109→      \"priority\": 3,\n   110→      \"passes\": false\n   111→    },\n   112→    {\n   113→      \"id\": \"US-008\",\n   114→      \"title\": \"Brain Age Results Score\",\n   115→      \"description\": \"As a user, I want to see my overall results as an engaging \\\"Brain Age\\\" style score so I can quickly understand how my attention compares to pre-digital norms.\",\n   116→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   117→        \"Composite score calculated from all completed tests, weighted by how far each metric deviates from baseline\",\n   118→        \"Presented as a \\\"Your Digital Attention Profile\\\" with a primary label, e.g., \\\"Your attention profile matches a typical 2024 heavy-social-media user\\\" or \\\"Your attention is in the pre-digital healthy range\\\"\",\n   119→        \"Visual score indicator (e.g., a gauge, spectrum bar, or animated number)\",\n   120→        \"Color-coded: green (healthy baseline range), yellow (moderate deviation), red (significant deviation)\",\n   121→        \"Brief 1-2 sentence summary of what the score means\",\n   122→        \"\\\"See detailed results\\\" expandable section (see US-009)\",\n   123→        \"Playful, non-clinical tone in the summary\"\n   124→      ],\n   125→      \"priority\": 4,\n   126→      \"passes\": false\n   127→    },\n   128→    {\n   129→      \"id\": \"US-009\",\n   130→      \"title\": \"Detailed Scientific Results\",\n   131→      \"description\": \"As a user, I want to expand my results to see detailed per-test breakdowns with scientific context, so I can understand exactly what was measured and how I compare.\",\n   132→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   133→        \"Each test has an expandable/collapsible section\",\n   134→        \"Per-test section shows: user's score, baseline norm, percentile or deviation indicator, and a chart/visual comparison\",\n   135→        \"Each section has a \\\"Learn more\\\" expandable that explains: what the test measures, why it matters, which study the baseline comes from (with citation)\",\n   136→        \"Citations link to actual papers (DOIs or URLs)\",\n   137→        \"All data comes from the sessionStorage results, no network calls needed\"\n   138→      ],\n   139→      \"priority\": 4,\n   140→      \"passes\": false\n   141→    },\n   142→    {\n   143→      \"id\": \"US-010\",\n   144→      \"title\": \"Shareable Results Link\",\n   145→      \"description\": \"As a user, I want to get a shareable link that encodes my results so I can send it to my parents or friends and they can see my scores without taking the test themselves.\",\n   146→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   147→        \"\\\"Share Results\\\" button on the results page\",\n   148→        \"All test results encoded into a compact string (e.g., base64-encoded JSON or a custom compact format) appended as a URL parameter or hash fragment\",\n   149→        \"When someone opens the shared URL, the app detects the encoded results and renders the results page directly (skipping tests)\",\n   150→        \"Shared results page shows a banner: \\\"These are [name/anonymous]'s results\\\" with a CTA \\\"Take the test yourself\\\"\",\n   151→        \"Copy-to-clipboard functionality with visual confirmation\",\n   152→        \"URL stays reasonably short (under ~2000 characters to be safe across browsers and messaging apps)\",\n   153→        \"Works when shared via iMessage, WhatsApp, Instagram DM\"\n   154→      ],\n   155→      \"priority\": 5,\n   156→      \"passes\": false\n   157→    },\n   158→    {\n   159→      \"id\": \"US-011\",\n   160→      \"title\": \"Session Progress Persistence\",\n   161→      \"description\": \"As a user, I want my test progress saved so that if I accidentally close my browser or refresh, I don't lose completed tests.\",\n   162→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   163→        \"After each test completes, results are saved to sessionStorage\",\n   164→        \"On app load, check sessionStorage for existing progress\",\n   165→        \"If progress exists, show option to \\\"Continue where you left off\\\" or \\\"Start over\\\"\",\n   166→        \"Starting over clears sessionStorage\",\n   167→        \"Progress includes: which tests are completed, raw results for each completed test\"\n   168→      ],\n   169→      \"priority\": 3,\n   170→      \"passes\": false\n   171→    },\n   172→    {\n   173→      \"id\": \"US-012\",\n   174→      \"title\": \"Pre-test Self-Report Questionnaire\",\n   175→      \"description\": \"As a user, I want to answer a brief questionnaire about my social media usage before the tests, so my results can be contextualized.\",\n   176→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   177→        \"4-6 quick questions: estimated daily TikTok/Reels/Shorts usage, age, how often they feel restless watching long videos, self-rated attention (1-5 scale)\",\n   178→        \"Questions presented as large tappable options, mobile-friendly\",\n   179→        \"Responses stored in sessionStorage and included in shareable link\",\n   180→        \"Results page references self-reported usage when presenting findings (e.g., \\\"You report 3+ hours daily on TikTok. Your sustained attention score is...\\\")\"\n   181→      ],\n   182→      \"priority\": 5,\n   183→      \"passes\": false\n   184→    }\n   185→  ]\n   186→}\n   187→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e06e47d8-12a6-4031-b9c7-f37052875646","uuid":"45d7c0f1-a8e7-4f57-bbc9-5134bc557399","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/janiszarzeckis/attention-span-test/.chief/prds/main/prd.json","content":"{\n  \"project\": \"Attention Span Test\",\n  \"description\": \"A static web app that presents users with a battery of scientifically-grounded cognitive tests measuring attention, impulse control, and focus duration. Results are compared against pre-social-media-era baselines from published research, presented as a fun \\\"Brain Age\\\"-style score, and expandable into detailed scientific breakdowns. The app targets teenagers (13-20) and their parents, is mobile-first (iPhone/iPad), and generates shareable links by encoding results in the URL.\",\n  \"userStories\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-001\",\n      \"title\": \"App Shell and Navigation\",\n      \"description\": \"As a user, I want a mobile-first app shell with smooth navigation between screens so that the experience feels native on my phone.\",\n      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n        \"Landing page with app title, brief tagline, and \\\"Start Test\\\" CTA button\",\n        \"Navigation flow: Landing -\\u003e Test sequence -\\u003e Results\",\n        \"Mobile-first responsive layout that works on iPhone SE (375px) through iPad (1024px)\",\n        \"Progress indicator showing which test you're on (e.g., \\\"Test 2 of 6\\\")\",\n        \"Uses shadcn components for UI elements\",\n        \"Built with Bun.serve() and HTML imports, React frontend\",\n        \"Deploys to Vercel as a static site\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 1,\n      \"passes\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-002\",\n      \"title\": \"Sustained Attention to Response Task (SART)\",\n      \"description\": \"As a user, I want to take a sustained attention test where I tap for every digit except one, so that my ability to maintain focus and inhibit impulses is measured.\",\n      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n        \"Digits 1-9 appear one at a time in the center of the screen at a fixed interval (~1150ms per stimulus, matching the original Robertson et al. 1997 protocol)\",\n        \"User must tap/click for every digit EXCEPT the target digit (3)\",\n        \"225 trials total (25 cycles of digits 1-9 in random order), taking ~4-5 minutes\",\n        \"Records: commission errors (tapping on 3), omission errors (missing a non-3 digit), mean reaction time (ms), reaction time variability (coefficient of variation = SD/mean)\",\n        \"Brief instruction screen before the test explaining what to do, with a practice round of 9 trials\",\n        \"Baseline comparison: healthy adult commission error rate of 8-11%, mean RT of 332-375ms\",\n        \"Results stored in sessionStorage upon completion\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 2,\n      \"passes\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-003\",\n      \"title\": \"Focus Duration Test\",\n      \"description\": \"As a user, I want to test how long I can sustain focus on a single piece of content before feeling the urge to skip, so I can see how my focus compares to pre-digital norms.\",\n      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n        \"Presents a mildly engaging but not thrilling stimulus (e.g., a passage of text that slowly reveals, a slowly changing visual pattern, or a calm narrated story)\",\n        \"User presses a \\\"I want to skip\\\" button whenever they feel the urge to move on\",\n        \"Timer runs visibly only after test completes (not during, to avoid anchoring)\",\n        \"Records: time until first skip urge, and whether they chose to continue or stop\",\n        \"Baseline comparison: Gloria Mark's research - 2.5 minutes (2004) vs. 40 seconds (2020s median)\",\n        \"Results stored in sessionStorage upon completion\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 2,\n      \"passes\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-004\",\n      \"title\": \"Stroop Color-Word Test\",\n      \"description\": \"As a user, I want to take a Stroop test that measures my ability to suppress automatic responses, so that my executive control is assessed.\",\n      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n        \"Three conditions presented in sequence: (1) read color words in black ink, (2) name ink colors of colored rectangles, (3) name the ink color of incongruent color words (e.g., \\\"RED\\\" displayed in blue)\",\n        \"Each condition: 20 stimuli, user selects from 4 color buttons (Red, Blue, Green, Yellow)\",\n        \"Records: accuracy and mean RT per condition, interference score (condition 3 RT minus condition 2 RT)\",\n        \"Brief instructions with 3 practice trials before the incongruent condition\",\n        \"Baseline comparison: interference effect norms stratified by age group\",\n        \"Results stored in sessionStorage upon completion\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 2,\n      \"passes\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-005\",\n      \"title\": \"Psychomotor Vigilance Task (PVT)\",\n      \"description\": \"As a user, I want to test my reaction time vigilance by responding to stimuli appearing at unpredictable intervals, measuring lapses in my attention.\",\n      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n        \"A stimulus (e.g., a red circle or counter) appears at random intervals between 2-10 seconds\",\n        \"User taps as fast as possible when the stimulus appears\",\n        \"30 trials, taking approximately 2-3 minutes\",\n        \"Records: median RT, number of lapses (RT \\u003e 500ms), number of false starts (tapping before stimulus)\",\n        \"Baseline comparison: healthy adult median RT of ~250ms, lapse rate \\u003c 5%\",\n        \"Results stored in sessionStorage upon completion\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 2,\n      \"passes\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-006\",\n      \"title\": \"Delay Discounting Task\",\n      \"description\": \"As a user, I want to make choices between smaller immediate rewards and larger delayed rewards, so that my impulse control and preference for instant gratification is measured.\",\n      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n        \"Series of 20-27 binary choices: e.g., \\\"$50 now\\\" vs \\\"$100 in 30 days\\\"\",\n        \"Amounts and delays adjust based on previous choices (staircase procedure) to find the indifference point\",\n        \"Choices presented as large tappable cards, mobile-friendly\",\n        \"Records: discount rate (k parameter from hyperbolic model), indifference points at multiple delays\",\n        \"Baseline comparison: normative k values for adolescents from published literature\",\n        \"Results stored in sessionStorage upon completion\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 3,\n      \"passes\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-007\",\n      \"title\": \"Go/No-Go Task\",\n      \"description\": \"As a user, I want to take a simple Go/No-Go test measuring my ability to withhold automatic responses, providing a quick measure of impulsivity.\",\n      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n        \"\\\"Go\\\" stimuli (e.g., green circles) appear frequently (80% of trials); \\\"No-Go\\\" stimuli (e.g., red circles) appear infrequently (20%)\",\n        \"100 trials total, stimulus duration ~500ms, ISI ~1000ms, taking ~2.5 minutes\",\n        \"User taps for Go stimuli, withholds for No-Go stimuli\",\n        \"Records: commission error rate (tapping on No-Go), omission error rate, mean RT, RT coefficient of variation\",\n        \"Baseline comparison: healthy adolescent commission error rate norms (decreases with age through ~16)\",\n        \"Results stored in sessionStorage upon completion\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 3,\n      \"passes\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-008\",\n      \"title\": \"Brain Age Results Score\",\n      \"description\": \"As a user, I want to see my overall results as an engaging \\\"Brain Age\\\" style score so I can quickly understand how my attention compares to pre-digital norms.\",\n      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n        \"Composite score calculated from all completed tests, weighted by how far each metric deviates from baseline\",\n        \"Presented as a \\\"Your Digital Attention Profile\\\" with a primary label, e.g., \\\"Your attention profile matches a typical 2024 heavy-social-media user\\\" or \\\"Your attention is in the pre-digital healthy range\\\"\",\n        \"Visual score indicator (e.g., a gauge, spectrum bar, or animated number)\",\n        \"Color-coded: green (healthy baseline range), yellow (moderate deviation), red (significant deviation)\",\n        \"Brief 1-2 sentence summary of what the score means\",\n        \"\\\"See detailed results\\\" expandable section (see US-009)\",\n        \"Playful, non-clinical tone in the summary\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 4,\n      \"passes\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-009\",\n      \"title\": \"Detailed Scientific Results\",\n      \"description\": \"As a user, I want to expand my results to see detailed per-test breakdowns with scientific context, so I can understand exactly what was measured and how I compare.\",\n      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n        \"Each test has an expandable/collapsible section\",\n        \"Per-test section shows: user's score, baseline norm, percentile or deviation indicator, and a chart/visual comparison\",\n        \"Each section has a \\\"Learn more\\\" expandable that explains: what the test measures, why it matters, which study the baseline comes from (with citation)\",\n        \"Citations link to actual papers (DOIs or URLs)\",\n        \"All data comes from the sessionStorage results, no network calls needed\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 4,\n      \"passes\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-010\",\n      \"title\": \"Shareable Results Link\",\n      \"description\": \"As a user, I want to get a shareable link that encodes my results so I can send it to my parents or friends and they can see my scores without taking the test themselves.\",\n      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n        \"\\\"Share Results\\\" button on the results page\",\n        \"All test results encoded into a compact string (e.g., base64-encoded JSON or a custom compact format) appended as a URL parameter or hash fragment\",\n        \"When someone opens the shared URL, the app detects the encoded results and renders the results page directly (skipping tests)\",\n        \"Shared results page shows a banner: \\\"These are [name/anonymous]'s results\\\" with a CTA \\\"Take the test yourself\\\"\",\n        \"Copy-to-clipboard functionality with visual confirmation\",\n        \"URL stays reasonably short (under ~2000 characters to be safe across browsers and messaging apps)\",\n        \"Works when shared via iMessage, WhatsApp, Instagram DM\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 5,\n      \"passes\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-011\",\n      \"title\": \"Session Progress Persistence\",\n      \"description\": \"As a user, I want my test progress saved so that if I accidentally close my browser or refresh, I don't lose completed tests.\",\n      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n        \"After each test completes, results are saved to sessionStorage\",\n        \"On app load, check sessionStorage for existing progress\",\n        \"If progress exists, show option to \\\"Continue where you left off\\\" or \\\"Start over\\\"\",\n        \"Starting over clears sessionStorage\",\n        \"Progress includes: which tests are completed, raw results for each completed test\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 3,\n      \"passes\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-012\",\n      \"title\": \"Pre-test Self-Report Questionnaire\",\n      \"description\": \"As a user, I want to answer a brief questionnaire about my social media usage before the tests, so my results can be contextualized.\",\n      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n        \"4-6 quick questions: estimated daily TikTok/Reels/Shorts usage, age, how often they feel restless watching long videos, self-rated attention (1-5 scale)\",\n        \"Questions presented as large tappable options, mobile-friendly\",\n        \"Responses stored in sessionStorage and included in shareable link\",\n        \"Results page references self-reported usage when presenting findings (e.g., \\\"You report 3+ hours daily on TikTok. Your sustained attention score is...\\\")\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 5,\n      \"passes\": false\n    }\n  ]\n}\n","numLines":187,"startLine":1,"totalLines":187}}}
